## Step 1 — Storage Setup

### 1.1 Add Dedicated Disks to Worker Nodes

Add an 800GB thin-provisioned disk to each worker node at the hypervisor level, then on each worker:

```bash
# Find the new disk
lsblk

# Partition (sdc on wk02/wk03/wk04, sdd on wk01)
fdisk /dev/sdc
# n → p → 1 → Enter → Enter → w

# Format
mkfs.xfs /dev/sdc1

# Get UUID
blkid /dev/sdc1

# Mount
mkdir -p /mnt/longhorn-data
echo "UUID=<uuid> /mnt/longhorn-data xfs defaults 0 0" >> /etc/fstab
mount -a

# Verify
df -h /mnt/longhorn-data
```

### 1.2 Add Disk to Longhorn

```bash
kubectl edit node.longhorn.io aamhilwk01.ttmtech.local -n longhorn-system
```

Add under `spec.disks`:

```yaml
spec:
  disks:
    default-disk-fd0300000000:
      allowScheduling: false    # disable OS disk for new volumes
      evictionRequested: false
      path: /var/lib/longhorn/
      storageReserved: 0
    longhorn-data:              # new dedicated disk
      allowScheduling: true
      evictionRequested: false
      path: /mnt/longhorn-data
      storageReserved: 10737418240
      tags:
        - data
```

Repeat for all 4 worker nodes.

