## Step 6 — Post-Deployment

### 6.1 Fix Ingress Class

After deployment patch all ingresses to use nginx:

```bash
for ingress in gitlab-kas gitlab-registry gitlab-webservice-default; do
  kubectl patch ingress $ingress -n gitlab \
    --type=json \
    -p='[{"op":"replace","path":"/spec/ingressClassName","value":"nginx"}]'
done
```

> **Note:** This is now permanent in the values file via `global.ingress.class: nginx`

### 6.2 CoreDNS — Internal DNS Resolution

The GitLab registry pod needs to resolve `minio-api.apps.ttmtech.com` internally:

```bash
kubectl edit configmap rke2-coredns-rke2-coredns -n kube-system
```

Add hosts block to the Corefile before the `forward` line:

```
hosts {
  10.45.17.118 minio-api.apps.ttmtech.com
  fallthrough
}
```

Restart CoreDNS to pick up the change:

```bash
kubectl rollout restart deployment rke2-coredns-rke2-coredns -n kube-system
```

